  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Social Mobilisation Study for Local Governance and Community Development Programme (LGCDP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project has four key objectives: 1: to review the effectiveness of social mobilisation processes against original intentions; 2: to examine the effects of the change in purpose of social mobilisation between the first LGCDP 1 programme to that of the revised LGCDP2 (from building a voice, to building of livelihood assets); 3: to review the effectiveness of institutional structures used to deliver social mobilisation; and 4: to look forward to describe possible mechanisms to build citizen engagement in local government.</narrative>
  </description>
